{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nExisting stores must learn they are behind the current binary's ensure set without paying\nhot-path cost — Rails `CheckPending` for a School-B registry: compare applied-set to the\nregistry's ids, nudge on write activity, cheaply, rate-limited, never breaking a write.\n\n## What\nRead `.ensure-applied` (WS1 owns its format: JSON array; absent/garbage → empty set) and\ncompute `pending = available_ids − applied_ids`, where `available_ids` = the ids in\n`ensures.py`'s registry. Compute this ONCE per process and cache the boolean (the registry is\nstatic within a process — no \"registry signature\" hashing needed). Hook the COMMON mutation\npaths via `_seam.append_event` / `event_append.write_and_push` (create/edit/link/comment/tag/\nset_*/sign/transition/claim) — lazy `import` inside the hook. This is best-effort, NOT\nuniversal: `compact.py`, `txn.py`/`transition_close.py`, `delete.py` commit inline and are\nintentionally NOT hooked (acceptable — a rate-limited nudge, not correctness). Emit a WARNING\npointing to `rebar fsck --fix` only when pending AND `.ensure-hinted` (WS2-owned: git-ignored,\natomic timestamp) is older than the interval; then atomically update `.ensure-hinted`.\n\nInterval + suppression are TYPED CONFIG routed through `_config_schema` + the env registry\n(NOT a raw os.environ read — there is a CI drift gate `gen_env_registry.py`):\n`ensure.hint_interval_secs` (default 86400) and `ensure.hint_enabled` (default true) with a\nregistered `REBAR_*` env override. The hook swallows ALL its own exceptions including\nlazy-import ImportError/SyntaxError and logs at debug — a write must never fail on it. A rare\ndouble-hint under parallel agents is accepted.\n\n## Scope\nIn: `.ensure-applied` read, compute-once-per-process cache, best-effort write-path hook,\n`.ensure-hinted` 24h rate-limit, typed-config interval + registered-env suppression,\nfail-silent (incl. import errors). Out: `run_ensures()` + `.ensure-applied` format/write (WS1),\n`fsck --fix` (WS3).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `pending = registry ids − parsed .ensure-applied` is computed once per process (cached boolean); a converged store adds ≤1 file read per process on writes and nothing after\n- [ ] Pure reads (show/list/search) are completely untouched — no marker read on the read path; the hook covers the common mutation paths and the inline-committer gap is documented as accepted\n- [ ] Hint points to `rebar fsck --fix`, rate-limited via `.ensure-hinted` (atomic timestamp) using `ensure.hint_interval_secs` (default 86400s); suppressible via `ensure.hint_enabled` + a registered env var (routed through `_config_schema`, passing the env-registry drift gate)\n- [ ] The hook swallows all its own exceptions including lazy-import failures (debug-logged); a write never fails because of it; no import cycle between `event_append` and `ensures.py`\n- [ ] A fresh auto-init'd worktree (WS1 wrote a current `.ensure-applied` at init) never hints; cross-reference WS1 for that guarantee"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783571781097891001,"uuid":"dd25f604-9e36-4475-b85a-0706eed151ff"}